### Reproduction

I have been having trouble with querying multiple agents. The first agent comes out okay, but any others i attempt to query i get an axios error. I have a functions for creating a chat model, crating a conversation chain, and creating an agent with tools and a memory using the two former functions. Here is my code

```js

	// Create OpenAI Chat instance
	const createChat = (model, temp) => {
		debug(`Creating chat ${model} temp ${temp}.`);
		return new ChatOpenAI({ temperature: temp, modelName: model });
	};
	
	// Create Chain (Memory) using LangChain
	const createChain = (model) => {
		// Define the chat prompt template with a MessagesPlaceholder to store the conversation history
		const chatPrompt = ChatPromptTemplate.fromPromptMessages([
			SystemMessagePromptTemplate.fromTemplate(
			"The following is a friendly conversation between a human and an AI. The AI is talkative and provides lots of specific details from its context. If the AI does not know the answer to a question, it truthfully says it does not know."
			),
			new MessagesPlaceholder("history"),
			HumanMessagePromptTemplate.fromTemplate("{input}"),
		]);
	
		// Create a ConversationChain with a BufferMemory to store the conversation history
		const chain = new ConversationChain({
			memory: new BufferMemory({ returnMessages: true, memoryKey: "history" }),
			prompt: chatPrompt,
			llm: model,
		});
		return chain
	};
	
	// Create agent with tools and memory using LangChain
	const createAgent = async (model, memory) => {
		const embeddings = new OpenAIEmbeddings();
		const tools = [
			new WebBrowser({ model, embeddings })
		];
		// Create agent with tools and memory
		const agent = await initializeAgentExecutorWithOptions(tools, model, { agentType: "chat-conversational-react-description" }, memory);
	
		return agent;
	}
	
	const easyAgent = async(llm, temp) => {
		const model = createModel(llm, temp);
		const chain = createChain(model);
		const agent = await createAgent(model, chain);
		return agent;
	}

```

The code works great! Until I try and make a new instance of an agent using the easyAgent() function. input values are 'gpt-3.5-turbo' for model and 0.5 for temp.

Here are the first agent i created with easyAgent()  
agent: https://pastebin.com/y6trG6t0  

Here are the second agent i create with easyAgent()
agent: https://pastebin.com/DhfNyV4z    

As you can see both instances of the agent are the exact same. There is no difference between the two. This is what leads me to believe the issue is with langchain. 

here is my error when i use the .call() method on the new agent:

```

Error: Request failed with status code 401
    at createError (C:\Users\Admin\Desktop\Code\LLM-Chat\node_modules\openai\node_modules\axios\lib\core\createError.js:16:15)
    at settle (C:\Users\Admin\Desktop\Code\LLM-Chat\node_modules\openai\node_modules\axios\lib\core\settle.js:17:12)
    at IncomingMessage.handleStreamEnd (C:\Users\Admin\Desktop\Code\LLM-Chat\node_modules\openai\node_modules\axios\lib\adapters\http.js:322:11)
    at IncomingMessage.emit (node:events:549:35)
    at endReadableNT (node:internal/streams/readable:1359:12)
    at process.processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:82:21)

```

All i can find relating to the issue is users running out of tokens or [this bug](https://github.com/openai/openai-node/issues/145)

### Expected behavior

I am expecting to be able to query the second agent just as i am the first.

